---
import { SITE } from "../data/site";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <main class="min-h-dvh">
    <section
      class="mx-auto flex min-h-screen w-full max-w-none flex-col px-8 py-7 sm:px-10 sm:py-8 lg:px-12"
    >
      <header
        class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 border-b border-foreground/20 pb-6 sm:gap-6"
      >
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <p
            class="font-ui-pixel text-xl leading-none tracking-tight sm:text-3xl"
          >
            {SITE.name}
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div
            class="font-ui-mono flex flex-nowrap gap-4 whitespace-nowrap uppercase tracking-widest sm:gap-6 text-[0.625rem] sm:text-xs"
          >
            <a
              href={SITE.links.github}
              target="_blank"
              rel="noreferrer"
              class="transition hover:opacity-70"
            >
              GitHub
            </a>
            <a
              href={SITE.links.chromeWebStore}
              target="_blank"
              rel="noreferrer"
              class="transition hover:opacity-70"
            >
              Add to Chrome
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="flex flex-1 flex-col pt-10 sm:pt-12 lg:pt-14">
        <h1
          class="font-ui-sans max-w-5xl text-balance text-6xl font-medium leading-[0.92] tracking-[-0.075em] sm:text-[5rem] md:text-[5.75rem] lg:text-8xl"
        >
          Extract shadcn-style theme tokens from sites that use them.
        </h1>

        <div
          class="mt-14 grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[8.5rem_minmax(0,1.05fr)_minmax(15rem,0.95fr)] lg:gap-10"
        >
          <div class="order-2 pt-1 lg:order-1">
            <div
              class="grid gap-2 sm:max-w-md lg:max-w-80 lg:gap-3 lg:border-l lg:border-foreground/20 lg:pl-5"
            >
              <div
                class="grid grid-cols-[4.75rem_1fr] items-baseline gap-x-3 font-ui-mono text-[0.625rem] uppercase tracking-widest lg:block lg:space-y-1 lg:text-[0.5rem]"
              >
                <p class="text-foreground/55 lg:text-foreground/70">Industry</p>
                <p>{SITE.meta.industry}</p>
              </div>
              <div
                class="grid grid-cols-[4.75rem_1fr] items-baseline gap-x-3 font-ui-mono text-[0.625rem] uppercase tracking-widest lg:block lg:space-y-1 lg:text-[0.5rem]"
              >
                <p class="text-foreground/55 lg:text-foreground/70">Scope</p>
                <p>{SITE.meta.scope}</p>
              </div>
              <div
                class="grid grid-cols-[4.75rem_1fr] items-baseline gap-x-3 font-ui-mono text-[0.625rem] uppercase tracking-widest lg:block lg:space-y-1 lg:text-[0.5rem]"
              >
                <p class="text-foreground/55 lg:text-foreground/70">Version</p>
                <p>{SITE.meta.version}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="order-1 space-y-8 lg:order-2">
            <p
              class="font-ui-sans max-w-136 text-4xl leading-[1.02] tracking-[-0.06em] sm:text-[2.75rem] lg:text-5xl"
            >
              Inspectcn extracts shadcn-style theme tokens from live interfaces
              using computed values without relying on incomplete source CSS.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="order-3 grid gap-7 font-ui-mono text-xs leading-5 text-foreground/75 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:order-3 lg:grid-cols-1"
          >
            <p>
              Through computed style sampling, Inspectcn reads what the UI is
              actually rendering and extracts shadcn-style theme tokens when
              they exist. That means you get the real token values in use, not
              whatever the source CSS suggests.
            </p>
            <p>
              The workflow is straightforward: install the extension, click the
              Inspectcn badge, and it reads the page and captures the token set.
              From there, copy the CSS variables or preview them locally before
              using them in your project.
            </p>
            <p>
              Inspectcn is still evolving. Open an issue for bugs or feature
              requests.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
